🐰 Spring 2023 Update
=======================


🛠️ Platform Improvements
--------------------------

(1) Capability Permission System

(2) Auto-differentiation

(3) GPGPU

(4) Sub headings

Previously, titles and subheadings were prepended with `#`, which could clash with the table declaration syntax. To resolve this issue, subheadings now have distinct formats for up to four different levels of headings. The new subheading format is as follows:

```
Title
=======

Subtitle
----------

(1) Subsection

(b) Sub-Subsection
```

(5) Downloading .mec files

We've added the addition of the ability to load/download `.mec` and `.blx` files to satisfy dependencies. 

Previously, the runtime could only download precompiled Rust machines. With this update, the you can now either download a `.mec` file and compile it, or download a precompiled `.blx` file and load it directly.

🐠 Ecosystem
--------------

(1) REPL Improvements

It is now possible to load `.mec` and `.blx` files from disk directly into the REPL using the `:load` command. For example, to load a file named `program.mec` in the current directory, you would run:

```
>: :load my_program.mec
```

In addition, it is now possible to save the state of the REPL into a `.blx` file using the `:save` command. This feature allows developers to save their work in progress and return to it later. To save the current state of the REPL into a file named `state.blx` in the current directory, you would run:

```
>: :save state.blx
```

